INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (400801, 'There is a passion for perfection which you rarely see fully developed  but... in successful lives it is never wholly lacking.', 8765, 0), (400802, 'Many of the most successful men I have known have never grown up. They have retained bubbling-over boyishness. They have relished wit  they have indulged in humor. They have not allowed "dignity" to depress them into moroseness. Youthfulness of spirit is the twin brother of optimism  and optimism is the stuff of which American business success is fashioned. Resist growing up!', 14130, 0), (400803, 'If you have the will to win  you have achieved half your success  if you don''t  you have achieved half your failure.', 63431, 0), (400804, 'Someone''s always saying  "It''s not whether you win or lose " but if you feel that way  you''re as good as dead.', 4803, 0), (400805, 'To bring one''s self to a frame of mind and to the proper energy to accomplish things that require plain hard work continuously is the one big battle that everyone has. When this battle is won for all time  then everything is easy.', 63432, 0), (400806, 'We would accomplish many more things if we did not think of them as impossible.', 63433, 0), (400807, 'Faith that the thing can be done is essential to any great achievement.', 63434, 0), (400808, 'We can accomplish almost anything within our ability if we but think that we can!', 62529, 0), (400809, 'Optimism is essential to achievement and it is also the foundation of courage and of true progress.', 10857, 0), (400810, 'Morale is the greatest single factor in successful wars.', 2119, 0), (400811, 'The will to conquer is the first condition of victory.', 62967, 0), (400812, 'The real secret of success is enthusiasm. Yes  more than enthusiasm  I would say excitement. I like to see men get excited. When they get excited they make a success of their lives.', 48343, 0), (400813, 'Always bear in mind that your own resolution to success is more important than any other one thing.', 1012, 0), (400814, 'It is fatal to enter any war without the will to win it.', 62961, 0), (400815, 'The measure of an enthusiasm must be taken between interesting events. It is between bites that the lukewarm angler loses heart.', 12943, 0), (400816, 'Enthusiasm for one''s goal to lessens the disagreeableness of working toward it.', 63435, 0), (400817, 'To burn always with this hard gemlike flame. To maintain this ecstasy  is success in life.', 11179, 0), (400818, 'Every man is enthusiastic at times. One man has enthusiasm for thirty minutes  another man has it for thirty days. But it is the man who has it for thirty years who makes a success in life.', 63436, 0), (400819, 'Man never rises to great truths without enthusiasm.', 62195, 0), (400820, 'Success is due less to ability than to zeal.', 12763, 0), (400821, 'I rate enthusiasm even above professional skill.', 63437, 0), (400822, 'He did it with all his heart  and prospered.', 5587, 0), (400823, 'A strong passion for any object will ensure success  for the desire of the end will point out the means.', 8948, 0), (400824, 'Nothing great was ever achieved without enthusiasm.', 760, 0), (400825, 'What a man accomplishes in a day depends upon the way in which he approaches his tasks. When we accept tough jobs as a challenge to our ability and wade into them with joy and enthusiasm  miracles can happen. When we do our work with a dynamic  conquering spirit  we get things done.', 62236, 0), (400826, 'If you''re not happy every morning when you get up  leave for work  or start to work at home-if you''re not enthusiastic about doing that  you''re not going to be successful.', 63438, 0), (400827, 'The method of the enterprising is to plan with audacity and execute with vigor.', 7233, 0), (400828, 'Do it big or stay in bed.', 63439, 0), (400829, 'Sometimes success is due less to ability than to zeal.', 12763, 0), (400830, 'Zeal will do more than knowledge.', 8948, 0), (400831, 'Let 