arn to wear it over one ear.', 8661, 0), (401137, 'Experience teaches only the teachable.', 1032, 0), (401138, 'Not to transmit an experience is to betray it.', 10, 0), (401139, 'Motives and purposes are in the brain and heart of man. Consequences are in the world of fact.', 63496, 0), (401140, 'Experience is a good teacher  but she sends in terrific bills.', 62388, 0), (401141, 'Experience is the best of schoolmasters  only the school-fees are heavy.', 3061, 0), (401142, 'A burnt child dreads the fire.', 41936, 0), (401143, 'Experience is the extract of suffering.', 62415, 0), (401144, 'I have but one lamp by which my feet are guided  and that is the lamp of experience.', 3269, 0), (401145, 'One thorn of experience is worth a whole wilderness of warning.', 1247, 0), (401146, 'Experience is the name men give to their follies or their sorrows.', 4004, 0), (401147, 'Men are wise in proportion  not to their experience  but to their capacity for experience.', 266, 0), (401148, 'Is there anyone so wise as to learn by the experience of others?', 808, 0), (401149, 'An expert is one who knows more and more about less and less.', 42167, 0), (401150, 'The shoemaker makes a good shoe because he makes nothing else.', 760, 0);
