INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (401251, 'You can beat the Bear once  but never the same way twice.', 63516, 0), (401252, 'Any man can make mistakes  but only an idiot persists in his error.', 20928, 0), (401253, 'There is nothing wrong with making mistakes. Just don''t respond with encores.', 33, 0), (401254, 'The road to wisdom? Well  it''s plain and simple to express: Err  and err  and err again. But less  and less  and less.', 2937, 0), (401255, 'I made a mistake today  I made a mistake yesterday. I think it''s ... very important to ignore the negative.', 63517, 0), (401256, 'The biggest quality in successful people I think is an impatience with negative thinking. ... How many opportunities come along? If you wait for the right one  that''s wrong  because it may never be right  and what have you got to lose? Even if it''s a disaster  you''ve tried  you''ve learned something  you''ve had an adventure. And that doesn''t mean you can''t do it again.', 63518, 0), (401257, 'A peacefulness follows any decision  even the wrong one.', 138, 0), (401258, 'If you don''t accept failure as a possibility  you don''t set high goals  you don''t branch out  you don''t try - you don''t take the risk.', 19480, 0), (401259, 'When we can begin to take our failures non-seriously  it means we are ceasing to be afraid of them. It is of immense importance to learn to laugh at ourselves.', 3172, 0), (401260, 'If I lose  I''ll walk away and never feel bad.... Because I did all I could  there was nothing more to do.', 14889, 0), (401261, 'A man must learn to forgive himself.', 63519, 0), (401262, 'You must accept that you might fail  then  if you do your best and still don''t win  at least you can be satisfied that you''ve tried.', 19480, 0), (401263, 'Who would not rather trust and be deceived?', 23259, 0), (401264, 'Forget mistakes. Forget failure. Forget everything except what you''re going to do now and do it. Today is your lucky day.', 1167, 0), (401265, 'There is a way to look at the past. Don''t hide from it. It will not catch you if you don''t repeat it.', 27040, 0), (401266, 'Forget your mistakes  but remember what they taught you.', 63520, 0), (401267, 'Supposing you have tried and failed again and again. You may have a fresh start any moment you choose  for this thing that we call "failure" is not the falling down  but the staying down.', 3277, 0), (401268, 'Failure is a disappointment but not defeat.', 63521, 0), (401269, 'Memories are the key not to the past  but to the future.', 533, 0), (401270, 'Failure is delay  but not defeat. It is a temporary detour  not a dead-end street.', 62349, 0), (401271, 'Finite to fail  but infinite to venture.', 91, 0), (401272, 'When in doubt  make a fool of yourself. There is a microscopically thin line between being brilliantly creative and acting like the most gigantic idiot on earth. So what the hell  leap.', 13133, 0), (401273, 'Failure really isn''t terrible if you can say to yourself  hey  I know I''m gonna be successful at what I want to do someday. Failure doesn''t become a big hangup then because it''s only temporary. If failure is absolute  then it would be a disaster  but as long as it''s only temporary you can just go and achieve almost anything.', 62406, 0), (401274, 'Failure is an event  never a person.', 10110, 0), (401275, 'It is better to be boldly decisive and risk being wrong than to agonize at length and be right too late.', 63522, 0), (401276, 'I''ve never met a person  I don''t care what his condition  in whom I could not see possibilities. I don''t care how much a man may consider himself a failure  I believe in him  for he can change the thing that is wrong in his life anytime he is prepared and ready to do it. Whenever he develops the desire  he can take away from his life the thing that is defeating it. The capacity for reformation and change lies within.', 5352, 0), (401277, 'I think and think for months  for years. Ninety-nine times the conclusion is false. The hundredth time I am right.', 104, 0), (401278, 'Take chances  make mistakes. That''s how you grow. Pain nourishes your courage. You have to fail in order to practice being brave.', 1180, 0), (401279, 'Take risks. You can''t fall off the bottom.', 63523, 0), (401280, 'When it goes wrong  you feel like cutting your throat  but you go on. You don''t let anything get you down so much that it beats you or stops you.', 63524, 0), (401281, 'You must have long-range goals to keep you from being frustrated by short-range failures.', 63525, 0), (401282, 'Life is a series of relapses and recoveries.', 9905, 0), (401283, 'We learn courageous action by going forward whenever fear urges us back. A little boy was asked how he learned to skate. "By getting up every time I fell down " he answered.', 63103, 0), (401284, 'If I had to live my life over again  I''d dare to make more mistakes next time.', 63526, 0), (401285, 'Failure is only postponed success as long as courage ''coaches'' ambition. The habit of persistence is the habit of victory.', 63081, 0), (401286, 'Entrepreneurs average 3.8 failures before final success. What sets the successful ones apart is their amazing persistence. There are a lot of people out there with good and marketable ideas  but pure entrepreneurial types almost never accept defeat.', 63527, 0), (401287, 'Success is going from failure to failure without loss of enthusiasm.', 3621, 0), (401288, 'I don''t accept defeat as final. Only death is final - and even then I hope for a reprieve.', 63528, 0), (401289, 'Never confuse a single defeat with a final defeat.', 97, 0), (401290, 'Men''s best successes come after their disappointments.', 2175, 0), (401291, 'I''ve been failing for  like  ten or eleven years. When it turns  it''ll turn. Right now I''m just tryin'' to squeeze through a very tight financial period  get the movie out  and put my things in order.', 28610, 0), (401292, 'Don''t let a kick in the ass stop you. It''s how you cope that says what you are.', 63524, 0), (401293, 'What is to be got at to make the air sweet  the ground good under the feet  can only be got at by failure  trial  again and again and again failure.', 12805, 0), (401294, 'They say President Wilson has blundered. Perhaps he has  but I notice he usually blunders forward.', 1673, 0), (401295, 'Some of the biggest failures I ever had were successes.', 442, 0), (401296, 'Not all who seem to fail have failed indeed. Not all who fail have therefore worked in vain. There is no failure for the good and brave.', 63529, 0), (401297, 'No honest work of man or woman "fails"  it feeds the sum of all human action.', 63530, 0), (401298, 'Defeat in doing right is nevertheless victory.', 29320, 0), (401299, 'The only failure a man ought to fear is failure in cleaving to the purpose he sees to be best.', 215, 0), (401300, 'Sometimes what you want to do has to fail so you won''t.', 63531, 0);
