o adjust immediately from a preconception to an actuality.', 1931, 0), (401439, 'We are less likely to fail if we measure with judgement our chances and our capabilities.', 24996, 0), (401440, 'Laziness is a secret ingredient that goes into failure. But it''s only kept a secret from the person who fails.', 2423, 0), (401441, 'Failure is usually the line of least persistence.', 63571, 0), (401442, 'You can''t expect to win unless you know why you lose.', 63056, 0), (401443, 'Most people don''t plan to fail  they fail to plan.', 63572, 0), (401444, 'Failure is not sweet  but it need not be bitter.', 33, 0), (401445, 'The ultimate umpire of all things in life is - fact.', 63573, 0), (401446, 'Losses are comparative  imagination only makes them of any moment.', 144, 0), (401447, 'I would prefer even to fail with honor than win by cheating.', 139, 0), (401448, 'Disillusion is a natural stage that follows the holding of an illusion.', 63574, 0), (401449, 'If any good results to a man from believing a lie  it certainly comes from the honesty of his belief.', 62850, 0), (401450, 'And what if I did run my ship aground  oh  still it was splendid to sail it!', 845, 0);
