h all this wide and beautiful creation before me  the restless soul longs to enjoy its liberty and rest beyond its bound.', 2751, 0), (401517, 'The country in which I live is not my native country  that lies elsewhere  and it must always be the center of my longings.', 4456, 0), (401518, 'The great majority of men use their own short-sighted ideas as a yardstick for measuring the divine omnipotence.', 4456, 0), (401519, 'Faith is the centerpiece of a connected life. It allows us to live by the grace of invisible strands. It is a belief in a wisdom superior to our own. Faith becomes a teacher in the absence of fact.', 9108, 0), (401520, 'Faith doesn''t wait until it understands  in that case it wouldn''t be faith.', 1887, 0), (401521, 'Your faith is what you believe  not what you know.', 45290, 0), (401522, 'That''s the thing about faith. If you don''t have it you can''t understand it. And if you do  no explanation is necessary.', 63587, 0), (401523, 'Our body is not made of iron. Our strength is not that of stone. Live and hope in the Lord  and let your service be according to reason.', 63588, 0), (401524, 'No  I don''t understand my husband''s theory of relativity  but I know my husband  and I know he can be trusted.', 63589, 0), (401525, 'It is faith  and not reason  which impels men to action. ... Intelligence is content to point out the road  but never drives us along it.', 62248, 0), (401526, 'Faith consists  not in ignorance  but in knowledge  and that  not only of God  but also of the divine will.', 4271, 0), (401527, 'Faith is an excitement and an enthusiasm  a state of intellectual magnificence which we must not squander on our way through life.', 810, 0), (401528, 'All the scholastic scaffolding falls  as a ruined edifice  before a single word: faith.', 1702, 0), (401529, 'Some like to understand what they believe in. Others like to believe in what they understand.', 63590, 0), (401530, 'Seek not to understand that thou mayest believe  but believe that tho